We call it the â€œcode battleâ€, and it's been going on for two months. 

It looks a great way for team members to come together and share their code style and coding logic.

Each week, one of our team members takes turns to come up with a problem. He abstracts an algorithm/data structure/refactoring problem from the business code, and then the others come together to implement it in 30 mins.
